<br>
Why not change the pet to be more dynamic?<br>
<br>
The idea has been buttered across these forums countless times.  Simple - make the epic scale as the mage caster himself levels.<br>
<br>
Levels 51-60, the epic pet will be level 49 like it is now:<br>
-4250hp, quads for 81, 143pt proc, 50pt DS, etc<br>
<br>
Levels 61-64, make the epic pet level 60.<br>
-4750hp, quads for 85, 156pt proc, 61pt DS, higher AC/Resist and greater ATK<br>
<br>
Level 65, make the epic pet level 62.<br>
-5500hp, quads for 91, 170pt proc, 63pt DS, even higher AC/resists and ATK.<br>
<br>
(Just ideas guys...)<br>
<br>
This keeps the epic, well, epic.  This allows players who don't get their epic to have a near epic pet as it is now, but also rewards the players who have gotten their epic to still receive the full benefits. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kylere>Kylere</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 342<br> <font color=#333333>(11/4/02 6:14:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7706.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Easy way to fix....</span><hr size=1> Mage epic should be a focus item for every pet a mage can summon, simple fix for VI to implement. It would make a good deal of sense, and as mages received the newer pets they would get a small 5-10% bump over non epic mages along with having a premana spent pet ready in rod, much as I have used an earth pet summons when things got tight and I was in between 5 minute recast of epic.  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=25992">Kylere Ap'Kailere -60th Archmage</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> //  Kailere Drowsbane -55th Paladin<br>
