<br>
First off, the epic needs to be a solid item.  How many of you guys really transfer your characters to other servers?  Point being, the epic should be the actual item and not a spell.  You shouldn't have to summon it.  It's just annoying.<br>
<br>
The epic should also retain its charge.  Obviously it would have to if the Orb of Mastery was no longer a summoned item.  =P  This is just common sense.<br>
<br>
Ditch the re-use time on the summoned pet.  This can be argued.  A chain summoned epic pet could be insanely deadly, but with a 26 second cast time (ala Khura's Focusing), do you really think you could time the chain correctly?<br>
<br>
This is just common sense stuff.  The mage epic is probably the most gruesome of them all, so why does it have to be the biggest pain in the arse after you get it?<br>
<br>
Just a thought. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zyrexxshadowfyre@themagicianstower>Zyrexx Shadowfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 456<br> <font color=#333333>(11/4/02 6:33:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7706.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pets, the new Order</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
