<br>
First, do we know for sure that there isn't an Epic 2.0 in PoP?  Something that requires the first epic as a starting place for a second upgraded item?  At this point we really do not know what is in store for us, but lets not rule this out completely.<br>
<br>
Second, VI doesn't look at our pets by themselves, they have the task of matching our own casting ability with the ability of our pets.  For example, they could have made our 61+ pets even more powerful than they are now, but then maybe we would not have received the DD upgrades recently give to us.  Many players have complained that pets are unusable on large raids, the increased DD power makes us more useful in these situations.  An increase the power of our pets would result in decrease in the power of our DDs by VI.  Do you really want this?<br>
<br>
As for wizards quad kiting PoP mobs around, I really don't think VI intended this.  I know many mobs in PoP were just altered so they couldn't be snared and / or rooted.  I don't think PoP is a place where VI intended any class to solo.  It was intended for some serious grouping.  In a group, our pets play a different roll that they have in the past.  What's the use of the 50 DS on our epic, if it very rarely, if ever, tanks?  I know people will argue about the soloing issue, but please also remember that PoD, PoJ, PoS, PoV, PoN are just the starting zones of this expansion (Newbie zones so to speak).  We still have a huge amount of unexplored content.<br>
